  <h1>
   string_set_byte_at
  </h1>
  This function sets a byte directly in a string (based on the UTF8 format) and returns a copy of the string with the changes.
  <span>
   NOTE
  </span>
  This function is incredibly slow so consider carefully whether it is necessary and where you use it.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">string_set_byte_at(str, pos, byte);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      str
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        String
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The string to change the byte of.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      pos
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The position within the string (starting at 1) to change the byte of.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      byte
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The new byte value.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 String
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">str = string_set_byte_at("hello", 2, 97);
</code></pre>
  The above code would change the byte value of the second letter in the string, and so set the variable
  <span>
   str
  </span>
  to hold "hallo".
 </body>
